            "title": "Novo Nordisk secures EU approval to streamline Wegovy delivery",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\">\n        \n                    Danish pharmaceutical giant Novo Nordisk has received EMA approval allowing its obesity drug Wegovy to be transported for up to 48 hours at temperatures reaching 30 degrees Celsius. This development significantly reduces the reliance on cold-chain logistics.<br/><br/>The company anticipates that this change will lower distribution costs, streamline logistics, and facilitate home deliveries via pharmacies and e-commerce platforms. No financial details were disclosed.<br/><br/>\"Home delivery of medicines is growing rapidly, driven by the convenience of having medications delivered directly to one's door – something we now expect in most other areas of our lives. Individuals with obesity using prescription medications can also face stigmatization, and we are therefore enthusiastic about the opportunity to simplify the distribution process while offering further discreet home delivery options,\" says Mike Doustdar, Executive Vice President at Novo Nordisk.\n    \n    </div>",
